<% title "Frequently Asked Questions"  %>
<div id="animated-banner">
    <h1>Help</h1>
    <h2>(AKA Frequently Asked Questions)</h2>
</div>

<div class="container">
<div class="col-xs-8 white-container">
<div class="panel-group" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">
  <h4><i class="fa fa-book"></i> General</h4>
  <%= render "faq_item", id:"sheethub-benefits", question: "What does SheetHub give me?", answer: "<p>SheetHub gives you the ability to self publish your sheet music/tablature/score online. You can easily create a page where your fans can view and purchase your works. Signing up also gives you an online profile that enables people to see and purchase all the works you've published on SheetHub. </p><p>All files are securely hosted on SheetHub so you don't need to worry about building a website or storing your files anywhere. Usage information is collected and displayed to you, such as how many times your music are being viewed, downloaded, and purchased.</p><p>SheetHub handles all the technical complexities behind hosting and selling your sheet music online, so you can focus on your musical pursuits. </p> " %>
  <%= render "faq_item", id:"sheethub-costs", question: "How much does SheetHub cost?", answer: "<p>SheetHub costs <strong>nothing</strong> to use. You are free to #{link_to 'sign up', new_registration_path(User)} and upload files without ever having to pay anything. SheetHub makes money by sharing revenue from online transactions. When someone buys your sheet, you receive 75% of the listed selling price. The remaining 25% goes to SheetHub as a fee for hosting your music and to fund awesome new features. Your royalties are paid directly and immediately to your PayPal account the moment a user purchases your music. SheetHub does not hold any of your net earnings.
    </p>" %>
  <%= render "faq_item", id:"earnings-calculation", question: "Someone buys my music for $8, how much do I get?", answer: "First, SheetHub will take 25% of the listed price, 2$. You receive the remaining 75%, 6$. The payment provider (PayPal) will take $0.30 + 2.9% of the total price, $8. Leaving you with $5.46."%>
  <%= render "faq_item", id:"howto-upload", question: "How do I upload my music on SheetHub?", answer: "After signing up, go to <strong>Upload</strong> and start publishing on SheetHub! You will need at least a printable PDF version of your sheet music to start. Adding detailed metadata about your piece, including Instruments, Composers, Genres, and Sources will help other users find your sheet more easily." %>
  <hr>

  <h4><i class="fa fa-music"></i> Sheet Music</h4>
    <%= render "faq_item", id:"sheet-requirements", question: "What technical requirements do you have for submitted PDFs?", answer: "PDFs submitted must be: <ul><li>sized for printing to 8.5 x 11 inches</li> <li>portrait oriented</li> <li>free of password protection</li> <li>less than 20 MB in size</li></ul><p>We require PDFs because it is a file format that is easily printable and require no specific music notation software installed to view. Users will be able to view and print your works without hassle.</p>"%>
     <%= render "faq_item", id:"sheet-recommendations", question: "Any other recommendations on how to format my PDF?", answer: "Users will be able to view a cover page which will be automatically created from the first page of your PDF. Customers are better able to make a purchasing decision if they can see a sample of your music that reflects the difficulty, range and uniqueness of your piece."%>
     <%= render "faq_item", id:"sheet-metadata", question: "What other information can I submit with my sheet music?", answer: "Submitting additional information about your sheet music - instruments, composers, genres, and sources - will help users find and ultimately purchase your sheet music. SheetHub also uses this information in our internal recommendations system. The more detailed information you provide, the more likely that your sheet music appears in recommended results. "%>
     <%= render "faq_item", id:"sheet-additional-files", question: "Can I add additional files together with my PDF?", answer: "<strong>Yes!</strong> You can add up to 5 supporting files such as audio files and music notation software specific files through your sheet's edit page. Each file must be less than 20MB in size. "%>
      <%= render "faq_item", id:"upload-limit", question: "How many sheets can I upload?", answer: "There is a soft limit of 25 sheets. The limit is in place to prevent abuse. If you wish to have more, then you should contact us." %>
      <%= render "faq_item", id:"howto-embed-links", question: "How can I link to my Youtube/Vimeo/Soundcloud?", answer: "<p>In your sheet description, you can add links to your hosted videos and SheetHub will automatically generate the video player for you. See an example below.</p> <img src='http://i.imgur.com/NoYhHmC.png' /><img src='http://i.imgur.com/ijjnhv6.png' /><p>Currently, Youtube, Vimeo, and Soundcloud embeds are supported. </p>" %>

  <hr>
  <h4><i class="fa fa-shopping-cart"></i> Purchases</h4>
    <%= render "faq_item", id:"my-purchases", question: "Where can I find my purchases?", answer: "You can view all your purchases on the <strong>Purchases</strong> page through the user dropdown. Click the individual files you wish to download from the sheet pages. Sheethub will generate an expiring, signed URL for you to start the download. "%>
  <hr>

  <h4><i class="fa fa-line-chart"></i> Payments, Sales, and Earnings</h4>
  <%= render "faq_item", id:"payment-flow", question: "How does SheetHub handle payments?", answer: "<p>SheetHub uses Paypal to process payments. PayPal is available in multiple countries and currencies, and accepts multiple modes of payment. Let's briefly walk through a buying user's purchasing flow. From your sheet's page, users will see a Buy Now button:</p>
    <img src='http://i.imgur.com/BazYJiN.png' />
    <p>Which will open a modal overlay:</p>
    <img src='http://i.imgur.com/RUCReKW.png' />
    <p>Clicking checkout will bring them to Paypal to authorize the purchase:</p>
    <img src='http://i.imgur.com/giJKV9C.png' style='width: 600px;'/>
    <p>Once the user has completed the authorization process, you will receive your earnings directly to your Paypal account. The user will, upon a successful purchase, be able to download the files you've uploaded for your sheet through SheetHub. Users cannot share their download links, as they are signed, expiring URLs. </p>
  "%>
  <%= render "faq_item", id:"sale-notification", question: "How do I know when I've made a sale?", answer: "<p>SheetHub will send a friendly email whenever you make a sale. It will be sent to the email address you registered with. If someone attempts to buy your music but the transaction cannot be completed (eg. due to invalid PayPal account information) then you will also be notified.</p><p>You can view detailed sales statistics - both recent and all-time sales - detailing who has bought your works, approximated earnings,  useful charts and other statistics from the <strong>Sales</strong> page. </p> "%>
  <%= render "faq_item", id:"paypal-transfer", question: "What do you need my PayPal Email for?", answer: "You need it to directly receive your sales earnings. SheetHub does not hold any of your net earnings, so we need a verified Paypal email account to directly send your earnings to. "%>
  <%= render "faq_item", id:"payment-information", question: "How do I update my payment information?", answer: "You can view and update your payment information by going to your profile <strong>Settings</strong> from the user dropdown."%>
  <%= render "faq_item", id:"payment-security", question: "Do you store my credit card information?", answer: "<strong>No credit card information is stored on our server!</strong> We use PayPal, one of the most secure and reputable payment processors available. PayPal automatically encrypts your confidential information in transit from your computer to ours using the Secure Sockets Layer protocol (SSL) with an encryption key length of 128-bits (the highest level commercially available.) Once your information reaches the PayPal site, it resides on a server that is heavily guarded both physically and electronically. PayPal servers sit behind an electronic firewall and are not directly connected to the internet, so your private information is available only to authorized computers. Visit <a href='https://www.paypal.com/sg/webapps/mpp/paypal-safety-and-security'>Paypal Security Center</a> for more details. "%>

  <hr>

  <h4><i class="fa fa-legal"></i> Publishing Rights and Copyright</h4>
